      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>While reading the list of ingredients for Worcestershire sauce was fascinating, and I understand the author's desire to break Worcestershire sauce down to its last molecule, this is one condiment that is best left undiminished.</p>
        <p>The British colonial administrator Lord Clive, upon viewing the Taj Mahal, could see the value only in its marble; likewise, there are those  who can see a masterpiece only as the sum of its parts.</p>
        <p>Worcestershire sauce should remain a mystery, sacrosanct in its  entirety.</p>
        <p>One hopes that, just as there will always be an England, there will always be a Lea &amp; Perrins.</p>
        <p>FRANCES CROUTER  Rhinebeck, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
